1
00:00:00,751 --> 00:00:01,710
[ Mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:01,793 --> 00:00:03,420
[ Penguins chirp ]

3
00:00:04,171 --> 00:00:05,088
[ Screeches ]

4
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:07,382
[ All cheering ]

5
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:10,844
[ Screeches ]

6
00:00:10,928 --> 00:00:12,054
[ Quacks ]

7
00:00:12,804 --> 00:00:13,931
s Adventure time J

8
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,349
J Come on, grab your friends &

9
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:18,018
J We're going to
a very distant land 7

10
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:20,521
s With Jake the dog
and Finn the human ;&

11
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:22,064
s The fun will never end J

12
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:24,274
J It's adventure time &

13
00:00:36,787 --> 00:00:37,871
Jake: Hey, brother.

14
00:00:38,622 --> 00:00:40,499
Pass me that jam,
won't you?

15
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:41,416
Finn: Sure.

16
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:43,085
Thanks.

17
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,465
[ Sniffling ]

18
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:51,343
So, how is your toast?

19
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:52,553
Pretty good.

20
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:56,473
Funny, though,
I can kind of taste

21
00:00:56,557 --> 00:00:58,141
the toast's emotions
or something.

22
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,311
Getting ground into flour
and then made into bread

23
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:03,897
really did a number on this
wheat's sense of self.

24
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:06,483
[ Whimpering ]

25
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:08,902
That's a pretty
hyper-developed

26
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:11,238
sense of taste
you've got there.

27
00:01:11,947 --> 00:01:14,575
Hey. You seem
kind of different.

28
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,119
Nope.
Same old Jake.

29
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:19,621
You're blue,

30
00:01:19,705 --> 00:01:20,789
you've got
those five eyes,

31
00:01:20,831 --> 00:01:21,832
you're way bigger,

32
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:24,251
and you keep discovering
strange new abilities.

33
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:26,420
I think this might be
a situation.

34
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:28,797
Where's this coming from?

35
00:01:29,256 --> 00:01:30,173
[ Gasps |

36
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:31,341
Whoops!

37
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:33,510
Tuck-tuck.

38
00:01:35,596 --> 00:01:36,555
See?

39
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:37,848
Same old Jake.

40
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:39,725
Ahhh!

41
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:40,559
Whoa.

42
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:43,228
Ahhh!

43
00:01:43,312 --> 00:01:46,732
Jack is a crab!
Ahhh!

44
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,276
Same old Jake.

45
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:50,444
If you say so.

46
00:01:50,736 --> 00:01:52,904
Hmm.

47
00:01:55,324 --> 00:01:58,410
I think I'm handling these
minor changes pretty well.

48
00:01:58,493 --> 00:02:01,496
Besides, a lot of people
are different these days.

49
00:02:02,706 --> 00:02:04,458
Dirt Beer Guy,
you're practically a zombie.

50
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:05,917
How are you dealing
with it?

51
00:02:06,001 --> 00:02:07,836
Well, I'm basically
the same as before.

52
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,838
The difference
is only physical.

53
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,633
So you agree Finn
is really overreacting?

54
00:02:12,758 --> 00:02:13,550
Totally.

55
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:15,636
You're the same person
as before.

56
00:02:16,053 --> 00:02:16,887
Heck yeah!

57
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,264
I'm still the same old Jake
on the inside.

58
00:02:19,348 --> 00:02:21,141
Wait, you're Jake?!

59
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:22,809
Uh, pardon me.

60
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:25,395
Oh, dear, oh, dear.
That's really something.

61
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:28,607
You know, I think I figured out
why I make people uneasy.

62
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:30,400
They're used
to yellow Jake.

63
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,361
[ Speaking Korean ]

64
00:02:35,364 --> 00:02:37,240
Mm-hmm.

65
00:02:39,117 --> 00:02:40,577
[ Grunts ]

66
00:02:42,537 --> 00:02:44,998
[ Laughs ]
Lady, that tickles.

67
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:46,458
[ Speaking Korean ]

68
00:02:47,334 --> 00:02:48,418
It's okay, lady.

69
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:50,629
Thanks for trying,
but I'm fine, really.

70
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:53,215
[ Speaking Korean ]

71
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:54,966
I love me, too.

72
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:57,636
Ruff!

73
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:00,347
Woof!

74
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:09,189
[ Music playing in distance ]

75
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,852
Ahhh!

76
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:48,979
Jermaine?

77
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:51,398
Ahh, mountain colors.

78
00:03:51,815 --> 00:03:53,191
I'm painting
this mountain.

79
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:57,279
I think it's really
coming together.

80
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,281
That's the mountain?

81
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:01,992
Yep.
I'm a mirror.

82
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:04,286
Hey, who's your friend?

83
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:06,705
Yipe!

84
00:04:09,249 --> 00:04:10,208
Dad?

85
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,418
Look at this.

86
00:04:12,002 --> 00:04:13,587
I can almost
walk the dog.

87
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:18,341
Your body looks like
one of my paintings.

88
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,385
Pretty weird dream, huh?

89
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:22,387
This isn't
just a dream body,

90
00:04:22,471 --> 00:04:25,015
this is what my body
looks like when I'm awake.

91
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,225
Oh. Got it.

92
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:29,060
Ha! I've got it!

93
00:04:29,144 --> 00:04:30,020
What?

94
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,064
I can almost
walk the dog.

95
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:39,029
Jake: Finn, you up?

96
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:40,530
Yeah, man.

97
00:04:40,614 --> 00:04:42,657
I had a really bad dream
last night.

98
00:04:42,866 --> 00:04:44,242
So ominous.

99
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:47,579
These images are going to haunt
me for, like, forever.

100
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:50,332
Sometimes it helps me
if I draw a bad dream

101
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:51,541
in picture form.

102
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,668
My crayons!

103
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:56,713
It was a weird scene,
all right.

104
00:04:56,797 --> 00:05:00,050
Chanting ladies, labyrinths,
classical sculpture.

105
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,927
And Jermaine
was there, too.

106
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:04,930
The weird thing was that he was
painting abstract art.

107
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:06,181
So?

108
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:09,392
F.Y.I., Jermaine hates
abstract art.

109
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:11,978
He would never paint something
non-representational.

110
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:14,898
Maybe he's just trying
something new?

111
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,399
It's not in his nature.

112
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:17,609
Why would he
all of a sudden

113
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:19,361
get into painting
meaningless shapes?

114
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,822
He's probably fine.

115
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:25,909
Just feels so out of character,
you know, for Jermaine.

116
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:27,744
How's the drawing?

117
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:32,999
Just squiggles.

118
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:35,585
Fuelish tank!

119
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:38,088
You are too slow
for the Finnosaurus.

120
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:40,006
Give up!
Give up!

121
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:43,593
Jake: I knew I had seen
that mountain.

122
00:05:45,637 --> 00:05:46,721
[ Scoffs ]

123
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:48,515
Tank boys,
you have no hope.

124
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:49,516
[ Laughs ]

125
00:06:03,822 --> 00:06:05,615
\VigaAVigaaVigad!

126
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:06,491
Brrt!

127
00:06:06,575 --> 00:06:07,617
Who goes there?!

128
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:09,911
James, it's me, Jake.

129
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:13,331
You look nothing like Jake,
but I believe you.

130
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:14,791
I just have to ask

131
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,877
because I'm supposed
to guard the Wasteland.

132
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:19,421
I was just making
some beans.

133
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:20,964
Come to my tent!

134
00:06:21,298 --> 00:06:23,925
Okay, but I don't
want any beans.

135
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:26,261
[ Laughs ] Man!

136
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:28,805
I could eat beans
all day, every day.

137
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:31,933
[ Gasps ] Where did you
get that painting?

138
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:35,353
One day when I was guarding,
I saw Jermaine painting it.

139
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:38,023
James was like, "Dang,
I like that painting!"

140
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,816
And he was like,
"You can have it."

141
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,401
And I was like,
"Waah?"

142
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:42,986
You like this?

143
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:45,113
It doesn't look anything
like a mountain.

144
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:47,365
I think you're looking
at it wrong.

145
00:06:47,449 --> 00:06:49,784
Where'd Jermaine go...
after?

146
00:06:49,868 --> 00:06:53,622
He went back to his studio,
behind the wall of water.

147
00:06:53,705 --> 00:06:54,998
You mean a waterfall?

148
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:57,167
No, like the thing
I said.

149
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:03,924
[ Laughing ]

150
00:07:04,007 --> 00:07:06,134
Hey! None but the
chosen may walk

151
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:07,886
beyond the wall
of water.

152
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,971
What have you done
with my brother?

153
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,557
Who's your brother?

154
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:13,808
Jermaine.

155
00:07:13,892 --> 00:07:16,853
Wow. You guys don't look
anything alike.

156
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:18,855
We're practically twins.

157
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:21,816
Well, I guess you can walk
beyond the wall of water.

158
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,568
But just this once.

159
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:26,279
Ooooh!

160
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:39,751
Can I help you, sir?

161
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:40,710
[ Chuckles ]

162
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:43,588
Hey, Bryce.
I'm looking for Jermaine.

163
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:45,924
Is he behind that door
marked "private"?

164
00:07:46,216 --> 00:07:47,425
No, no, no.

165
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:49,552
Mr. Jermaine won't be seeing
anyone today.

166
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:52,389
His wishes for privacy
were quite explicit.

167
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,391
You wouldn't want to interrupt
Mr. Jermaine.

168
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,725
He's a brilliant painter.

169
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:57,310
Yeah, he used to be.

170
00:07:57,394 --> 00:07:59,896
Now you got him painting
all this nonsense.

171
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:01,773
I'm just his humble dealer.

172
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,900
So many times
I've watched him

173
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:07,862
painting,
painting, painting.

174
00:08:08,154 --> 00:08:10,115
What's really going on,
Bryce?

175
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:12,784
My dad told me
all about your demon tricks.

176
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:16,579
Well, now I don't want to say
anything bad about your dad,

177
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:17,622
but...

178
00:08:17,706 --> 00:08:20,333
[ Blows landing, grunting ]

179
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:25,463
[ Muffled words ]

180
00:08:33,388 --> 00:08:35,223
Bro?
I'm here to save you.

181
00:08:35,306 --> 00:08:36,307
Hmm?

182
00:08:36,391 --> 00:08:37,392
Oh. Hey.

183
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,352
I'm not sure
if this is done yet.

184
00:08:39,436 --> 00:08:42,063
It's hard to tell when an
abstract is finished.

185
00:08:42,272 --> 00:08:44,190
Jermaine,
what's wrong with you?

186
00:08:44,274 --> 00:08:47,068
Who's taken away your identity
as a landscape painter?

187
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,070
There's nothing wrong
with me, Jake.

188
00:08:49,154 --> 00:08:50,530
I just changed a little.

189
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,116
You seem like you've changed
a little bit, too.

190
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:55,285
No, I just look different.

191
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:57,662
Eh, that sounds
like denial.

192
00:08:57,746 --> 00:08:58,621
No, it doesn't!

193
00:08:58,705 --> 00:08:59,873
Come on, bro.

194
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:02,625
Nothing's different!
I'm the same!

195
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,252
Same old Jake!

196
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:07,505
Completely... normal!

197
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:08,923
[ Groans ]

198
00:09:09,841 --> 00:09:11,342
This looks bad,

199
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:14,220
but deep down,
I'm not different.

200
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:16,056
And you're not different
either, right?

201
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:18,349
You'll go back
to painting landscapes.

202
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,228
No one
is making me do this.

203
00:09:22,312 --> 00:09:25,648
I painted so many landscapes
that the shapes of the land

204
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:27,609
began to lose
their meaning.

205
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,986
And the shapes
broke apart to me,

206
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,030
so I painted them
like that.

207
00:09:32,489 --> 00:09:34,157
And it's not like
my new paintings

208
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,617
erase my old paintings.

209
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:37,494
They're both me.

210
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:38,912
Okay.

211
00:09:38,995 --> 00:09:40,997
I think I'm starting
to get it.

212
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:43,124
I like the new look,
by the way.

213
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,169
'‘Cause you like your brothers
to be crazy shapes?

214
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,087
Sure.

215
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:50,882
Also, Dad told me you might go
through some changes one day.

216
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:52,092
Huh?

217
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:53,843
He told me
to be supportive.

218
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:56,179
But I would've
done that anyway.

219
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:57,597
I wonder what he meant.

220
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,682
You know
how secretive Dad was.

221
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,643
Sorry I don't have
more answers.

222
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,896
Well, do you have
any more of these paintings?

223
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,867
The shapes are always changing.

224
00:10:18,493 --> 00:10:21,371
Changing is their normal state,
like us.

225
00:10:21,538 --> 00:10:23,748
Even if we're not changing
on the outside,

226
00:10:23,832 --> 00:10:25,708
we're changing
on the inside constantly.

227
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:27,544
There's some stuff about me

228
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,254
that I've been ignoring
for a long time.

229
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:31,047
I'm afraid of that stuff.

230
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:33,049
But it's part of who I am.

231
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:36,386
As long as I know the shape of
my soul, I'll be all right.

232
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:41,349
Wow. You really
understand my art.

233
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,935
Oh, I totally
don't understand anything.

234
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:46,563
[ Both laugh ]

235
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:49,732
[ Whistling ]

236
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:55,238
Hey, you're back.

237
00:10:55,405 --> 00:10:58,199
Yeah, I went to see Jermaine.
He says hi.

238
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:01,077
No, I mean, like,
you're really back.

239
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:02,745
Huh?

240
00:11:04,873 --> 00:11:06,499
Different, yet the same.

241
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:15,758
J Come along with me J

242
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:20,013
s And the butterflies and bees &

243
00:11:22,974 --> 00:11:25,185
This party is so crazy!

